# cursor-schedule Project Conventions

## File Structure
- Every source file starts with a relative path comment (`# src/cursor_schedule/store.py` or `// gnome-extension/.../extension.js`).
- Files are <=100 lines. If approaching the limit, split by concern.

## Python
- Absolute imports within the package: `from cursor_schedule.store import TaskStore`. No relative imports.
- ESM-style modules only. No CommonJS patterns.

## GJS (GNOME Extension)
- ESM imports: `import ... from './taskStore.js'`. No legacy GJS `imports.` syntax.

## Module Boundaries
- `store.py` owns `tasks.json` -- no other module reads/writes it directly.
- `systemd.py` owns unit files -- no other module calls `systemctl` directly.
- `cli.py` orchestrates store + systemd; it is the only entry point for mutations.
- `taskStore.js` is the only GJS module that calls CLI subprocesses or reads `tasks.json`.

## Naming
- systemd units are always `cursor-task-<id>`. No other prefixes.
- Task IDs are lowercase alphanumeric + hyphens. No underscores, no spaces.

## AI Shebang
- Enforced on all `.py` and `.js` files per the global ai-shebang rule.
